Emmet. The Prisoner was not gone before I fell asleep, but she was gone before I was awake. - The Prisoner fell asleep, and I believe we all fell asleep. - I have had my Watch again: She confessed before the Alderman that she took it, and told that Gentleman (
William Jones
) where it was pawn'd, and that it was pawn'd for 22 s. 6 d. I heard her say, she took it from under the Bolster.

Rachael Sheppard
. I am Servant to Mr Monk; I saw the Prisoner come out of the Drinking-Room at my Master's, (the Horshoe in Blowbladder-Street
) with this Chamber-pot under her Apron: I suspected she had stolen the Pot, and run into the Room, locked where it used to stand, and found it was gone. I told my Fellow Servant of it, and he went after her, and took it from her; this is very much like the Pot that was taken out of the Drinking-Room.
